### Step 2

Add the conditional CSS Style

> Default Styles when the active class hasn't been applied

```css 

/* Hide .answer Child by default by setting height to 0 and overflow hidden*/

.accordion .content-container .answer {
    padding-top: 15px;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.5;

    /* Accordion Effect */
    height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;

    /*  Smooth Effect */
    transition: .5s;
}
```

> Conditional CSS Style Below, this works with  Element.toggle()

```css
/* Javascript Toggle Class */
/* Content Container Parent element with the class of active target child .answer */
.accordion .content-container.active .answer {
    height: 100px;
}
```


### Step 3

Attach event listener to the HTML collection using for loop

> The -this- keyword can be only used with function declaration and not with arrow functions.


```js 
// Select Element
const accordion = document.getElementsByClassName("content-container")


// For loop to attach event listeners to all the elements
for (let i = 0; i < accordion.length; i++) {
    accordion[i].addEventListener("click", (event) => {


        // Select the Current Element Parent
        const currentElement = event.target.parentElement


        //   Attach/Remove the class to parent Element of Selected Item
        currentElement.classList.toggle('active')
    })
}

```

> The for loop attach event listeners to these elements

